column2: Sun- 90 F.  3 boats and water skiing.
Water Temp 80- saw 2 baby loons and 2 adult loons.
Cloudy skies.  Observed one adult loon and one juvenile loon.  Water had greenish tint.   Water Temp 75
Water seems somewhat murkier after heavy rains in June.  No baby loons noted this year.  Bald eagles have been spotted this year.
Water color does not seem to be as brown as last year and clarity has improved.  Loon babies born two weeks ago- but the bad news is they were killed by a power boat on 7/6/18.
Large amounts of rain this year- water seems to be more dingy and less clear than other years.  2 adult and 2 baby loons now seem to be down to 1 adult and one baby loon.
